{"questionId":"10663","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Bromine and methanoic acid react in aqueous solution.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Br<sub>2</sub> (aq) + HCOOH (aq) → 2Br<sup>−</sup> (aq) + 2H<sup>+</sup> (aq) + CO<sub>2</sub> (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The reaction was monitored by measuring the volume of carbon dioxide produced as time<br>progressed.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/678d23bae9495ae4a3337049953f74911a3c8d7b.png\" width=\"701\" height=\"486\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Identify <strong>one</strong> error associated with the use of an accurate stopwatch.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">human reaction time/delay «starting/stopping the stopwatch»&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10663","referenceCode":"19M.3.hl.TZ2.2c(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify one error associated with the use of an accurate stopwatch.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.1 Uncertainties and errors in measurement and results","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}